<title type="html"><![CDATA[Level Editors]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1515&amp;p=12987#p12987"><![CDATA[
IMO, levels are a very personal thing. Since you are the one coding the game engine, you should come up with a format that is easy for your engine to work with.<br /><br />If you just use someone else's format, you'll end up wasting a lot of time figuring out how to work with their format, and may not come up with an optimum solution.<br /><br />I think you should understand how such a game works first, and then create your own level format, that works best with the engine you created.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue May 16, 2006 9:19 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
