I'd suggest learning how to program in C on a PC first. Then you'll have enough experience to be able to understand 1. the explanations in a 6502 tutorial and 2. what a game loop looks like.<br /><br />If you're not ready for that, I'd suggest getting an editor from romhacking.net or zophar.net.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon May 15, 2006 9:53 pm</p><hr />
